experiments were conducted at various currents (C/2 and C/10) to

profiles of purpurin at current rates of C/2, C/10 and C/20 are
shown in Figure 1(c). The contour of the voltage
curve at higher current rates of C/2 is very similar to the one

discharge cycle at a current rate of C/20 is much higher than that of
C/10 and C/2. The decrease in specific capacity at higher current
rates is due to poor electron conductivity of purpurin molecule. We
